%N A397867 Decimal expansion of the volume of a canonical (dual-uniform) heptagonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397867 The heptagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the heptagonal antiprism.
%H A397867 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397867/b397867.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A397867 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalTrapezohedron.html">Heptagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397867 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antitegum">Heptagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397867 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397867 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_03">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 3</a>.
%F A397867 Equals (7*(1 + 2*cos(Pi/7))*cot(Pi/14)*csc(Pi/14)^2)/(24*sqrt(2*(1 + cos(Pi/7)))).
%F A397867 Equals the largest root of 216*x^3 - 7812*x^2 - 7350*x - 343.
%e A397867 37.085373785330227003772190307850040514791996579912...
%t A397867 First[RealDigits[Root[216*#^3 - 7812*#^2 - 7350*# - 343 &, 3], 10, 100]]
%t A397867 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397867 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 7}, "Volume"], 10, 100]]
%Y A397867 Cf. A397868 (surface area), A397869 (inradius), A397870 (midradius), A397871 (height).
%Y A397867 Cf. A397872 (long edge).
%Y A397867 Cf. A397873 (small face angle), A397874 (large face angle), A397875 (dihedral angle).
%Y A397867 Cf. A394071 (volume of the dual).
%K A397867 nonn,cons,easy,new
%O A397867 2,1
